case_data.name: Metabolic Fatigue Syndrome
case_data.chief_complaint: I feel exhausted all the time, no matter how much I sleep
case_data.prognosis: Good with early intervention and lifestyle changes, though recovery may take 3-6 months
case_data.description: A subclinical metabolic disorder characterized by chronic fatigue without clear organic cause, often related to modern lifestyle factors including poor sleep patterns, nutritional deficiencies, and chronic low-grade stress. Distinct from chronic fatigue syndrome by its reversible nature with preventive interventions.

chat_history.content: Hey there. *shifts uncomfortably in chair* I'm Eric... I've been feeling completely drained for months now, no matter how much rest I get. I finally decided I needed to come in and figure out what's going on.
